\begin_layout Subsubsection
Markets with Growing Inventors' Share Experienced Increased Patent Litigation
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In this section, I restrict my attention to the period 2002 to 2012 for
 which data on patent litigation cases are available.
 I employ the same specification as in (
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "eq: spec"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

), but now I difference the data over the horizon 2002-2012, using as dependent
 variable the number of litigations per 1000 patents, computed as described
 in Section 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "subsec:Other data and aggregation"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

.
 I weight the regressions by the number of patents registered in each sector
 in 2012, as this drives a significant amount of the variance of the measure
 of litigations per patents.
 This is to avoid that sectors with very few patents drive the results.
\begin_inset Foot
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout
For example, I have 3 patents for NAICS sector 4539 for the Economic Census
 year 2012 and 2 litigations per patent, compared to 0 litigations in the
 2002 census year.
 This implies an increase of 2000 litigations per patent, compared to an
 unweighted sample average of 22.6.
\end_layout

\end_inset

 Table 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "tab: RegLitigations"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

 displays a strong and sizable correlation between increases in inventor
 shares and litigations per patent.
 The baseline specification in column (2) implies that 1pp increase in the
 share of inventors employed by a sector was associated with and increase
 of 3.6 litigation cases per 1000 patents.
 This compares to a cross-sector weighted average increase of 1.33 litigations
 per 1000 patents.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Float table
wide false
sideways false
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\begin_inset Caption Standard

\begin_layout Plain Layout
